<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAURICE HEXTER; FUND-RAISER FOR JEWISH CAUSES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Maurice Hexter, 99, a major fund-raiser for Jewish causes in British-mandate 
Palestine and across the United States. 
</P>
<P>
Hexter joined the the Federation of Jewish Philanthropies of New York in 1938 
on his return from Palestine, and by 1967, as executive vice president, 
distributed nearly $500 million to its health and welfare agencies. In 1929, he 
moved to Jerusalem to administer the Palestine Emergency Fund, which collected 
millions of dollars worldwide to rebuild homes wrecked by rioting between Arabs 
and Jews. He also was a former executive director of the Milwaukee Federation 
of Jewish Charities. In New York on Oct. 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
