<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: HEMACARE REPORTS LOSS FOR 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HemaCare Corp., a Sherman Oaks-based provider of blood-related services and 
products, reported a $290,000 loss for the third quarter, compared with a 
$126,526 profit a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The loss in the quarter that ended Sept. 30 came despite a 48% jump in 
HemaCare's revenue, to $2.18 million from $1.47 million. The company blamed the 
loss on costs associated with its new clinical laboratories business and to 
research projects. 
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months of 1990, HemaCare lost $523,594 compared with 
year-earlier earnings of $333,328. Its nine-month revenue climbed 38% to $5.78 
million from $4.18 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
