<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: CAMERA PLATFORMS LOSES $679,128 IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Camera Platforms International Inc., a Valencia provider of production 
equipment to the movie and television industries, said it lost $679,128 in the 
third quarter, compared with a year-earlier loss of $744,090. 
</P>
<P>
The narrower loss came on a sharp rise in Camera Platforms' revenue, to 
$681,750 in the quarter ended Sept. 30 from $349,597 a year earlier. Continuing 
demand for the company's lighting products contributed to the gains, Camera 
Platforms said. 
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months of 1990, the company lost $1.26 million on revenue of 
$3.26 million. A year earlier, it lost $2.23 million on revenue of $1.13 
million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
