<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: K-SWISS EARNINGS JUMP 68% DURING 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
K-Swiss Inc., a Pacoima maker of athletic shoes and other footwear, reported a 
68% jump in third-quarter earnings on a 38% increase in sales. 
</P>
<P>
In the quarter that ended Sept. 30, K-Swiss' net income rose to $3.12 million 
from $1.86 million a year earlier, while its sales climbed to $31.6 million 
from $22.9 million. 
</P>
<P>
K-Swiss' profit for the first nine months of this year totaled $6 million, up 
49% from $4.04 million a year earlier, and its nine-month sales rose 41% to 
$78.6 million from $55.6 million the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
