<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: AMERICAN RESTAURANTS' QUARTERLY PROFIT RISES 78% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
American Restaurants Corp., extending a recent rebound in earnings, said its 
third-quarter profit soared 78% from a year earlier on an 18% increase in 
sales. 
</P>
<P>
The Ventura-based company, which operates Hudson's Grill and Wendy's 
restaurants, said net income in the quarter ended Oct. 1 rose to $264,682 from 
$148,390, while sales climbed to $7.37 million from $6.23 million. It was the 
company's seventh straight increase in quarterly earnings. 
</P>
<P>
For the first nine months of this year, American Restaurants' net income jumped 
58%, to $593,460 from $376,410, and its nine-month sales rose 16% to $21.5 
million from $18.6 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
