<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: PERCEPTRONICS EARNINGS FOR 3RD QUARTER DOWN 73% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Perceptronics Inc. in Woodland Hills said its third-quarter earnings plunged 
73% from a year earlier on a 36% decline in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
The company, which makes computer-based simulators and other equipment for the 
military, said net income in the quarter that ended Sept. 30 fell to $104,099 
from $378,110 a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
Its revenue dropped to $4.73 million from $7.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
Perceptronics attributed much of the declines to the winding down of its 
contract on SIMNET, a project that enables tank gunnery simulators to fight 
each other over a computer network. 
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months of this year, Perceptronics' profit fell 48% to 
$253,638 from $491,706 a year earlier, and its nine-month revenue was down 23% 
to $10.9 million from $14.1 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
