<P>
SUTTON NEEDS SURGERY, OUT A MONTH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ram cornerback Mickey Sutton, scheduled to undergo arthroscopic surgery on his 
left knee today, is expected to be sidelined for at least a month. 
</P>
<P>
Complicating the picture in the secondary, the status of injured cornerback 
Jerry Gray remains a question. 
</P>
<P>
"We're not looking for any miracles right now," Coach John Robinson said of 
Gray, who did not play Sunday because of a sore left knee. "You keep hoping 
that all of a sudden the Pro Bowl cornerback would come back. But that just 
hasn't happened. Until he can come back in good fashion, we just can't press 
him. We will just have to take that day by day." 
</P>
<P>
The Rams hope to shore up their secondary losses with Darryl Henley, who on 
Sunday made a successful comeback from a hip injury. Also, Clifford Hicks, who 
has been the physically unable to perform list all season with a knee injury, 
might be available. 
</P>
<P>
Robinson continued to be vague about when he plans to activate running back 
Marcus Dupree from the injured-reserve list. "At some point," Robinson said. 
With Sutton out, there will be an open roster spot for Dupree this week, if 
Robinson chooses to use it that way. TIM KAWAKAMI 
</P>
</TEXT>
