<P>
ROYSTER RUNNING AT 1,000-YARD PACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In five games as USC's starting tailback, sophomore Mazio Royster has rushed 
for 642 yards and six touchdowns in 119 carries, averaging 128.4 yards a game 
and 5.4 yards a carry. 
</P>
<P>
In Saturday's 31-31 tie against California, he ran for 175 yards and two 
touchdowns in 24 carries, averaging 7.3 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Royster needs to average 72.5 yards in USC's last four games, including a 
probable bowl appearance, to become the first Trojan sophomore to rush for 
1,000 yards since 1977, when Charles White rushed for 1,478. 
</P>
<P>
The starting time for USC's game against Oregon State Saturday at Corvallis, 
Ore., has been changed to 3:30 p.m. to accommodate Prime Ticket, which will 
televise the game. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
