<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
European golf officials threatened to pull stars such as Nick Faldo and 
Severiano Ballesteros out of the Ryder Cup because of rifts between the event's 
organizing bodies, the Professional Golfers' Assn. and the PGA European Tour. 
</P>
<P>
Europe's Ryder Cup captain, Bernard Gallacher, also threatened to quit if the 
differences are not resolved soon. 
</P>
<P>
The Ryder Cup, played every two years between teams from the United States and 
Europe, is held by the European team. 
</P>
<P>
Ken Schofield, executive director of the European Tour, said most major 
differences over money and organization have been resolved, but a stumbling 
block appears to be a PGA suggestion that the agreement should be reviewed in 
12 years. 
</P>
