<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: BERLIN; 
</P>
<P>
A DOUBLE ANNIVERSARY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A series of official functions, including a plenary session in the old 
Reichstag building of the German Parliament's upper house, will mark Friday's 
first anniversary of the collapse of the Berlin Wall. 
</P>
<P>
In the 12 months since the announcement echoed around the world, much of the 
wall has been completely removed, and within months the remnants are expected 
to disappear. 
</P>
<P>
Friday is also the anniversary of Crystal Night -- the 1938 attacks by Nazis 
and their sympathizers on Jews and Jewish property that were an ominous hint of 
the Holocaust to come. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
