<P>
PEDESTRIAN DIES AFTER BEING HIT BY CARS ON FREEWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A pedestrian died Monday evening after being struck by several vehicles on the 
Ventura Freeway in Calabasas, the California Highway Patrol reported. 
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred at 6 p.m. on the eastbound Ventura Freeway east of 
Parkway Calabasas, said CHP Officer Robert Strong. 
</P>
<P>
The identity of the victim had not been determined because of the battered 
condition of the body. "We assume it was a male," said Capt. Richard Leitch of 
the Los Angeles County Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
Witnesses told authorities "they'd seen someone walking along the freeway," 
Leitch said, but investigators found no abandoned car. 
</P>
