<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMAN, 22, KILLED IN CAR ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 22-year-old Port Hueneme woman died late Monday after being ejected from a 
subcompact car that was struck broadside while spinning out of control, 
California Highway Patrol officers said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, whose name was being withheld, was pronounced dead at Las Robles 
Regional Medical Center in Thousand Oaks at 8:35 p.m.,Officer David Webb said. 
</P>
<P>
Webb said the woman was in the back seat of a Datsun driven by Cammie Hoyt, 23, 
of Port Hueneme. 
</P>
<P>
Her car was struck by a Ford driven by Richard Gardner, 42, of Camarillo, who 
was unhurt, Webb said. 
</P>
<P>
Webb said Hoyt, who is four months pregnant, and a 12-year-old girl in the car 
suffered minor injuries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
