<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE RIGHT COURSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles City Councilman Ernani Bernardi's support of uninterrupted play on 
the three Sepulveda golf courses is applauded by members of the Sepulveda Men's 
Golf Club. 
</P>
<P>
Our 800-member club has for a long time urged the use of Tillman reclaimed 
water to irrigate these courses in an effort to alleviate a four-year drought. 
Tearing up the courses to lay water mains to carry Tillman water can be 
self-defeating. Reduced fees for shortened courses could cost the city about as 
much as routing those pipes around them. 
</P>
<P>
Keep up the good fight. 
</P>
<P>
SAM BENSUSSEN, Sherman Oaks. Bensussen is secretary of the Sepulveda Men's Golf 
Club. 
</P>
