ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: BUENA PARK; 
</P>
<P>
CITY NAMES DIRECTOR OF DEVELOPMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thomas E. Lynch, a former official of Riverside County, has been hired by the 
city to serve as director of its Developmental Services Department. 
</P>
<P>
Lynch, who began his duties this week, was head of community development for 
Riverside and, previously, for Palm Springs. He is replacing James DeStefano, 
who resigned earlier this year to take a job with the city of Burbank. 
</P>
<P>
As director, Lynch will manage the city's planning, building and code 
enforcement activities. He also will oversee redevelopment of the 
"entertainment corridor" along Beach Boulevard and other commercial areas. 
</P>
<P>
He holds a master's degree in public administration from UC Berkeley. 
</P>
</TEXT>
