<P>
CORONA DEL MAR GETS TOP BILLING IN 5-A VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Corona del Mar High School is the top-seeded team in the Southern Section 5-A 
girls' volleyball playoffs, which begin tonight. 
</P>
<P>
The Sea Kings (18-1) will play the winner of the wild-card match between 
Estancia and Redondo Beach in a first-round match Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
Wild-card matches in the 5-A, 3-A, 2-A and Small Schools divisions begin 
tonight. First-round matches in all divisions are Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
Other top teams in the 5-A Division are second-seeded Laguna Beach, 
third-seeded El Toro and fourth-seeded Capistrano Valley. 
</P>
<P>
In the 4-A playoffs, Cypress will meet Long Beach Poly, Fountain Valley will 
play Los Alamitos and Esperanza will meet Edison Thursday in first-round 
matches. 
</P>
<P>
In the 3-A playoffs, defending champion La Habra will play the winner of the 
Foothill-Santiago wild-card match in the first round Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
In the 2-A Division, Anaheim will play a first-round matches at Atascadero. 
</P>
<P>
Three Orange County teams will play first-round matches in the 1-A Division. 
Capistrano Valley Christian will play host to Bassett, Whittier Christian will 
play host to Pasadena Poly, and Orange Lutheran will play at South Hills. 
</P>
<P>
In the Small Schools Division, Pacific Shores will play a first-round match at 
St. Margaret's and Santa Ana Calvary Chapel will play the winner of the 
Shandon-First Lutheran wild-card match. 
</P>
