</P>
<P>
All games begin at 3:15 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Defending 4-A champion Corona del Mar, the second-ranked team in the county, 
was also among the wild-card teams announced Monday by the Southern Section 
office. 
</P>
<P>
A forfeited league game dropped Corona del Mar (22-4) into a tie for the Sea 
View League title, but the Sea Kings lost a subsequent coin flip. Newport 
Harbor and University received the league's two playoff berths, and Corona del 
Mar will play at Esperanza (10-5) Wednesday. The winner will play Friday at 
second-seeded Sunny Hills. 
