<TEXT>
<P>
BellSouth Corp. said today it will offer early retirement to as many as 3,000 
managers in an effort to streamline its operations. 
</P>
<P>
The special early retirement option for eligible managers begins Dec. 1, said 
Roy Howard, BellSouth senior vice president of human resources. 
</P>
<P>
"To respond to the increasingly competitive telecommunications marketplace, we 
must continually introduce structural and operating efficiencies," Howard said. 
</P>
<P>
Management employees working for BellSouth's regulated and unregulated 
companies will be offered the early retirement, which will include a special 
one-time payment to managers who agree to leave within a designated time frame 
at the company's discretion. 
