<TEXT>
<P>
George Foreman, who is scheduled to meet newly crowned world heavyweight 
champion Evander Holyfield for the title at Atlantic City in April, will fight 
in an exhibition bout Nov. 20. 
</P>
<P>
Foreman, 41, who has won 22 straight bouts since ending a 10-year layoff in 
1987, has agreed to appear in a four-round, no decision bout at the Sherwood 
Club, promoter Fred Berns said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Berns said he hopes to match Foreman against either former world 
light-heavyweight champion J. B. Williamson or Dickie Ryan, a former Nebraska 
all-state football player who is in the United States Boxing Assn.'s top 10. 
</P>
<P>
The eight-round main event of the Nov. 20 card will pit welterweight Terry 
Thomas of Lafayette against Jimmy Duke of Norman, Okla. 
