'WON'T DIET AGAIN,' OPRAH SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oprah Winfrey has put back on quite a few of the 67 pounds she shed during a 
crash diet two years ago, but she has no plans to starve herself thin again. 
</P>
<P>
"I'll never diet again," the talk show host told her audience Monday. "I 
certainly will never fast again." 
</P>
<P>
Winfrey announced in 1989 that she had regained 17 of the 67 pounds she had 
lost the year before on a diet that consisted of weeks of drinking a 
high-protein powder mixed with water. 
</P>
<P>
She didn't disclose her weight Monday. 
